Men's Health Recommendations: 
Women's Health Recommendations: Visit a general practitioner or a gynaecologist for a Pap smear and a Radiologist for a mammogram annually.
Overview Notes: Supplement with vitamin D3 5000iu daily, aiming for a blood level of 50 to 80ng/ml. Recheck levels in 4 months.

Doctor: Christie Pilossof

Clinical Recommendations: A full hearing test is recommended as a mild decrease in hearing was identified in one frequency in your left ear.  The rest of your hearing test is within normal limits.
Men's Health Recommendations:

Women's Health Recommendations: Visit a Radiologist for a mammogram once you turn 40.
Overview Notes: Insufficient vitamin D level
High fasting insulin level
Mild normocytic normochromic anaemia

Comment Value: None
Special Investigation Notes: Leukocytes and blood in urine but no nitrates and asymptomatic

Men's Health Recommendations: 
Women's Health Recommendations: Visit a general practitioner or a gynaecologist for a Pap smear and a Radiologist for a mammogram annually.
Overview Notes: Mild normocytic normochromic anaemia. Possibly due to very heavy periods. Has copper IUD since last child born and periods have been heavy ever since. Suggest follow up with gynae for a sonar.

Clinical Recommendations: Normal clinical examination on the day.
Men's Health Recommendations: 
Women's Health Recommendations: Visit a Radiologist for a mammogram once you turn 40.
Overview Notes: Insufficient vitamin D level
High fasting insulin level
Mild normocytic normochromic anaemia
Comment Key: LabTestNote
Comment Value: MIld normocytic normochromic anaemia, mild neutropenia, low vitamin D, raised fasting insulin
Special Investigation Notes: Leukocytes and blood in urine but no nitrates and asymptomatic

Women's Health Recommendations: Visit a Radiologist for a mammogram once you turn 40.
Overview Notes: Mild normocytic normochromic anaemia. Possibly due to very heavy periods. Has copper IUD since last child born and periods have been heavy ever since. Suggest follow up with gynae for a sonar.
Comment Key: MedicalHistoryRecommendation
Comment Value: Choose a healthy lifestyle to reduce your risk for developing familial related chronic illnesses.
Special Investigation Notes: Leukocytes and blood in urine but no nitrates and asymptomatic

Overview Notes: Mild normocytic normochromic anaemia. Possibly due to very heavy periods. Has copper IUD since last child born and periods have been heavy ever since. Suggest follow up with gynae for a sonar.
Comment Key: MentalHealthAnxietyRecommendation
Comment Value: None
Special Investigation Notes: Leukocytes and blood in urine but no nitrates and asymptomatic

Men's Health Recommendations: 
Women's Health Recommendations: Visit a Radiologist for a mammogram once you turn 40.
Overview Notes: Mild normocytic normochromic anaemia. Possibly due to very heavy periods. Has copper IUD since last child born and periods have been heavy ever since. Suggest follow up with gynae for a sonar.

Special Investigation Notes: Leukocytes and blood in urine but no nitrates and asymptomatic
